<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Environmental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Protection </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> has added six major estuaries to a list of ecologically sensitive coastal areas targeted for study on ways to improve their health and clean them up. Placed on the list Monday were <LOCATION> Galveston </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Inland </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Del </PERSON>.; the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York-New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Harbor </LOCATION>; <LOCATION> Sarasota </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>; and <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Monica </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>. Estuaries _ where rivers meet the sea, and fresh water mixes with salt water _ serve as the principal spawning grounds and nurseries for at least two-thirds of the nation's commercial fisheries and are home to valuable and diverse species of fish, shellfish and wildlife, the <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION> said They also are sources of `` irreplaceble recreation and aesthetic enjoyment,'' the agency said. `` Estuaries are clearly in trouble, threatened by toxic and bacterial contamination, industrial and municipal sewage discharges, agricultural runoff, oxygen-depleted waters and loss of fish and wildlife habitat,'' said <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION> regional administrator <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Layton </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION>. Under the National Estuary Program, the bay studies are designed to come up with recommendations for long-term strategies for pollution control and resource management, <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION> officials said. <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION> spokesman