<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Natural disasters killed 529 people and caused $ 540 million in damage in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> in the first half of this year, an official newspaper reported today. The <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> Daily, quoting a <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Affairs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> official, said floods, drought, landslides and cold spells also injured 11,588 people, destroyed 470,000 homes and affected 64 million of <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>'s 1.07 billion people Disasters also damaged $ 2.4 million homes and killed 90,000 horses and oxen, it said. Most the deaths and injuries were caused by floods that ravaged large areas of southern <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> last month, washing away at least $ 1.1 billion pounds of grain. The report said 65.8 million acres of land have been affected by drought, which has dried up crops in 18 provinces in central, southern and western <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>. Another 24.7 million acres has been hit by floods. <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> has about 296 million acres of arable land. The daily said the <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Affairs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> had allocated $ 130 million in disaster relief. It did not give comparative figures for casualties and damage in 1987. In 1986, natural disasters claimed 5,381 lives, injured 40,396 and destroyed 2 million homes. The government that year spent $ 384 million to help disaster victims.
