<BYLINE>By LINDSEY TANNER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A writer who had to borrow money for treatment after he was disabled in an accident received one of 31 <ORGANIZATION> MacArthur </ORGANIZATION> awards announced today and said he will use the money `` to pay the people who take care of me until I die.'' Fiction writer <PERSON> Andre </PERSON> <PERSON> Dubus </PERSON> said he felt `` gratitude so extreme that I have n't recovered from it yet.'' Like other recipients, <PERSON> Dubus </PERSON>, whose latest book was `` The Last Worthless Evening,'' learned of his award last week. `` I've been using borrowed money for the people who take care of me,'' said <PERSON> Dubus </PERSON>, 51, in an interview Monday from his <LOCATION> Haverhill </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass. </LOCATION>, home. He was injured and had a leg amputated two years ago after he was hit by a car while helping another motorist. He said he plans to invest his $ 310,000 grant so that he will have enough money to pay for his treatment and caregivers for the rest of his life. <PERSON> Dubus </PERSON>, whose work has concentrated on discontented <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Englanders </LOCATION>, has already won a Guggenheim grant, the PEN-New <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> Award for literary distinction and an award from the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Academy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arts </ORGANIZATION> and Letters. Last year <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> King </PERSON>, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>, <PERSON> Kurt </PERSON> <PERSON> Vonnegut </PERSON>, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Updike </PERSON> and other authors gave a series of readings to help raise $ 100,000 for <PERSON> Dubus </PERSON>' treatment. Other MacArthur winners include a firefighter who studies the cultural history of fires, noted jazz percussionist <PERSON> Max </PERSON> <PERSON> Roach </PERSON> and the gr