1986. All leading anti-apartheid organizations have been banned, including the <ORGANIZATION> ANC </ORGANIZATION>, which is the main guerrilla group fighting the government. Since the government silenced 17 leading anti-apartheid groups in February it has not tolerated even relatively minor demonstrations.
