 </ORGANIZATION> says he is a distant relative of the former governor. `` We're not quite as clean as people would like to have you believe,'' <PERSON> Hauda </PERSON> said. `` You have to judge things based on community standards, just like obscenity. Based on <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>'s standards, we've got some problems here. <PERSON> Hauda </PERSON>'s group said <PERSON> Goyke </PERSON>'s wife, attorney <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Rottier </PERSON>, gave thousands of dollars to more than 30 legislators' campaigns, which she defended as her right. <PERSON> Hauda </PERSON> argued that was a method used by lobbyists to circumvent lobbying restrictions. <ORGANIZATION> Milwaukee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Magazine </ORGANIZATION> has not said what its article will say, but some legislators have admitted taking favors from <LOCATION> Goyke </LOCATION>. State Rep. <PERSON> Gordon </PERSON> <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> accepted a $ 5 or $ 6 fish dinner from <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> Otte </PERSON>, a former legislator and employee of <LOCATION> Goyke </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Wausau </LOCATION> Mayor <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON>, a former state representative, failed to report $ 247 in air fares for members of his family accepted from <ORGANIZATION> Pfizer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, one of <PERSON> Goyke </PERSON>'s clients, to a <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> health-care conference at which <PERSON> Robinson </PERSON> spoke. Several legislators attended a <ORGANIZATION> Green </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bay </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Packer-Chicago </ORGANIZATION> Bears game in <LOCATION> Green </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION>, possibly at <PERSON> Goyke </PERSON>'s expense. State Sen. <PERSON> Jerome </PERSON> <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Sistine </PERSON> acknowledged accepting two nights of lodging in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> during his honeymoon as 