<HEAD>Bright and Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTAGE, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police Officer <PERSON> Rick </PERSON> <PERSON> Flynn </PERSON> is down in the dumps. But that's easy to understand because he's patrolling in a dump truck. The only police car in this eastern <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> community of about 3,500 broke down this week, and officials were concerned about possible insurance problems if officers used their own cars. So officials gave police the borough's dump truck. `` People who see me in the dump truck think it's funny,'' <PERSON> Flynn </PERSON> said. `` I think it's funny, unless I'm driving it. That thing bounces a lot.'' <PERSON> Flynn </PERSON> said the police car should be repaired Wednesday.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Howe </PERSON> paid out nearly $ 60 and a lesson in human nature to students in his remedial math class this summer. In return, he got his students' attention, and that was worth every penny, <PERSON> Howe </PERSON> says. When <PERSON> Howe </PERSON> walked into his summer school class of fourth - and fifth-graders at <ORGANIZATION> Southside </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Elementary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> last month, he knew that motivating 18 students in the heat of summer would be difficult `` I thought, ` Why not pay them? I'm getting paid to be here, so why not them?''' <PERSON> Howe </PERSON> said. The students were told they would be paid up to 20 cents per day, depending on attendance, behavior and performance. `` It gives them a purpose for being here. Students have to have goals to achieve, and this gave them something as a goal,'' <PERSON> Howe </PERSON> said. The change in attitude was almost immediate. `` They were aware of it when I put their name on the board -LRB- for misbehaving -RRB-. They knew they were losing money,'' the teacher said. Payday was Friday, the end of the term. Students were paid $ 4.70 down to $ 1.70. No one got the maximum $ 5 for the six-week session. `` They left a little richer than they came in, in one way or another. If that makes a lasting impression, then it was worth it,'' he said.
