 The head of the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Family </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> says <ORGANIZATION> Universal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION> will be committing `` financial suicide'' if it releases the movie, `` The Last Temptation of Christ.'' The Rev. <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Wildmon </PERSON>, executrive director of <ORGANIZATION> AFA </ORGANIZATION>, says he sent copies of the script to 200 top Christian officials and those who have read it are appalled. `` It is absolutely the most perverted, distorted account of the historical and biblical Jesus I have ever read,'' says <PERSON> Wildmon </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Methodist </ORGANIZATION> minister. Thew movie, based on a novel by <PERSON> Nikos </PERSON> <PERSON> Kazantzakis </PERSON>, was scheduled to be released this fall.
