<TEXT>
 In the face of drought across <ORGANIZATION> mid-America </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Bishop </PERSON> <PERSON> Herbert </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Chilstrom </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> Evangelical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lutheran </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, urges prayers in all its congregations that God `` send rain to the thirsty ground.''
