<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The American Jewish <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> says a <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION> law recognizing Good Friday as a legal holiday violates the Constitutions's ban against establishing religion. The friend-of-court brief was filed with the federal appeals court after a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> district court in <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION> had upheld the holiday, saying it gave residents a needed day of rest to do as they chose. The day commemorates the crucifixion of Christ.
