<DATELINE>PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A Gallup survey conducted shortly after <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> was reported to consult an astrologist found that 80 per cent of Americans do not believe in astrology. The poll of l ,204 adults found that only 12 percent believe that movement of heavily bodies influence human events, while 8 percent said they do n't know However, 25 percent of Americans regularly read astrology columns, although they're considerably more skeptical about it than in 1978, when 29 percent said they believed in it.
