<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Relics have been returned to the Russian Orthodox Church from state museums in the <LOCATION> Kremlin </LOCATION>, including relics of the apostle <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON>, <PERSON> George </PERSON> the dragon slayer and <PERSON> John </PERSON> the Baptist, the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> news agency <ORGANIZATION> Tass </ORGANIZATION> reports. Also included was material venerated as part of the cross on which <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON> was crucified, the robes of <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON>' mother and the Gospel writers <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> and <PERSON> Matthew </PERSON>, and the stone used to seal <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON>' tomb
