<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A three-year agreement has been signed between the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Methodist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Global </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministries </ORGANIZATION> and a newly formed employees' association covering 193 non-executive staff members. The agreement, which replaces a union agreement, provides for a pay increase of 7 percent this year, 6 percent in 1989 and 5 percent in 1990.
