<HEAD>``Full Metal Jacket''@ (Warner Home Video; VHS-Beta, $89.95;</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 Rated R -RRB- <PERSON> Stanley </PERSON> <PERSON> Kubrick </PERSON> was at a disadvantage when `` Full Metal Jacket'' hit the nation's movie screens last summer. <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> Stone </PERSON>'s `` Platoon'' had already nabbed Academy Awards, including best picture, and helped galvanize a nation around the haunting reminders of a terrifying time Other Vietnam War movies also had floated by: <PERSON> Francis </PERSON> <PERSON> Coppola </PERSON>'s `` Gardens of Stone,'' <PERSON> Lionel </PERSON> <PERSON> Chetwynd </PERSON>'s `` The Hanoi Hilton'' and <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Irvin </PERSON>'s `` Hamburger Hill. Still, <PERSON> Kubrick </PERSON>'s electrifying excursion into military mania managed to snare its share of the moviegoing audience. In fact, film buffs had long awaited <PERSON> Kubrick </PERSON>'s next work, seven years after `` The Shining,'' and were curious to see how he would treat the madness of <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> after depicting modern insanities in `` Paths of Glory,'' `` 2001: A Space Odyssey'' and `` Dr. <PERSON> Strangelove </PERSON>, Or How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Bomb.'' Based on <PERSON> Gustav </PERSON> <PERSON> Hasford </PERSON>'s gripping novel, `` The Short Timers,'' <PERSON> Kubrick </PERSON>'s work actually is two movies with the same characters: The first part, and by far the best, takes place at <LOCATION> Parris </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> S.C. </LOCATION>, where recruits are stripped of their humanity to become killing machines; the second part shifts to <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>, where the marines fight the Tet offensive. We see the best of <PERSON> Kubrick </PERSON>'s talents in `` Full Metal Jacket'' _ the title refers to the casings on the bullets _ in the slick editing and direction of Gunnery Sgt. <PERSON> Hartman </PERSON> working the last nerves of his boys. `` You will be ready to eat your own guts and ask for seconds,'' he tells them. <PER