<HEAD>Icahn: Still Mulling Options After Texaco Defeat</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RICK GLADSTONE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Takeover strategist <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> says he still has a myriad of options to pursue despite his defeat in a June proxy fight attempt to win a block of seats on <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors. <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> management on Monday confirmed earlier estimates that shareholders rejected <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>'s attempt to place himself and four associates on the board. <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>'s dissident slate was voted down by 58.6 percent to 41.6 percent, a much bigger margin than earlier thought. <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>, who owns a 14.8 percent chunk of <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> stock, had conceded defeat after the oil giant's annual shareholder meeting, but had contended the vote was close. There had been speculation <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> was awaiting the exact results to determine how close he came to winning before deciding what to do with his <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> investment. Some Texaco-watchers speculated that a narrow vote might prompt <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> to challenge the outcome or make another attempt to get on the <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> board as part of a broader campaign to acquire the company or force a restructuring that would raise the value of his shares. `` We obviously regret that we lost, but hope that management will do as they said and work to enhance stockholder value,'' <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> said in a statement issued by D.F. <ORGANIZATION> King </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, the firm that handled his proxy campaign. `` To answer the many queries concerning our position, there are a myriad of options open to us at this time,'' he said. `` We have not yet determined which one we will follow.'' <ORGANIZATION> Te