<HEAD>Posts 43 Percent Profit Hike in 2nd-Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday its second-quarter profit climbed 43 percent from a year earlier, reflecting growth in its agricultural, sweetener, chemical and electronic materials businesses. The company said it earned a record $ 220 million, or $ 3.04 per share, in the three months ended June 30 compared with $ 154 million, or $ 1.95 per share, a year earlier. Second-quarter sales rose 11.3 percent to $ 2.26 billion from $ 2.03 billion a year earlier. For the first six months of 1988, net income reached a record $ 430 million, or $ 5.90 per share, up 47 percent from a profit of $ 292 million, or $ 3.71 per share, a year earlier. Six-month sales rose 12.9 percent to $ 4.39 billion from $ 3.89 billion a year earlier. Chairman <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON> said the results indicate that `` we are making significant progress toward achieving our long range financial goal of 20 percent return on equity by the early 1990s.'' <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> is specializes in pharmaceuticals, agricultural products, specialty chemicals, low-calorie sweeteners, industrial controls and electronic materials. The <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agricultural </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> fueled the growth of second-quarter earnings with significant sales growth of Roundup and Lasso herbicides and <PERSON> Alimet </PERSON> poultry feed supplement, <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> said. The <ORGANIZATION> NutraSweet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> also had a strong quarter, reflecting continued growth for products containing the artificial sweetener, <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> said. Results from the quarter also included accelerated shipments to certain customers to meet production scheduling requirements. That will likely be reflected in somewhat lower volume shipments in the second half of the year, <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> said. Its <PERSON> G.D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Searle </PERSON>, <PERSON> Fisher </PERSON> Controls and <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electronic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Materials </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> also showed strong improvements, <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> said.
