<HEAD>Drug Manufacturers Report Higher Second Quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<HEAD>By The Associated Press</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 The nation's leading drug manufacturers reported double-digit increases in both profits and worldwide sales of their health-care products for the second quarter. <ORGANIZATION> Bristol-Myers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Eli </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lilly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Upjohn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> reported gains in both domestic and overseas operations. Bristol-Myers, based in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, reported net income of $ 190.5 million, or 66 cents a share, up 18 percent from $ 161.5 million, or 56 cents a share a year ago. Revenue totaled $ 1.46 billion, up 11 percent from $ 1.31 billion in the second quarter of 1987. For the first half, <ORGANIZATION> Bristol-Myers </ORGANIZATION> reported net earnings of $ 401.13 million, or $ 1.39 a share, on revenue of $ 2.98 billion, compared with net income of $ 335.39 million, or $ 1.17 a share, on revenue of $ 2.66 billion in the first six months of 1987. <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION>, also based in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, reported net income of $ 215.8 million, or $ 1.48 a share, up 10 percent from $ 195.9 million, or $ 1.33 a share in the year ago period. Revenue totaled $ 1.37 billion, up 12 percent from $ 1.23 billion a year ago. For the first six months, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> reported net income of $ 452.9 million, or $ 3.10 a share on revenue of $ 2.78 billion. In the first half of 1987, net income totaled $ 412.3 million, or $ 2.78 a share, on revenue of $ 2.52 billion. Indianapolis-based <ORGANIZATION> Lilly </ORGANIZATION> reported second-quarter net income of $ 180.7 million, or $ 1.27, up 21 percent from $ 150.3 million, or $ 1.03 a share a year ago. Sales for the quarter totaled $ 1.01 billion, up 10 percent from $ 925.9 million last year. For the first six months, <ORGANIZATION> Lilly </ORGANIZATION> reported net income of $ 413.9 million, or $ 2.89 a share, on sales of $ 2.09 billion. In the previous year, the company reported earnings of $ 355.5 million, or $ 2.42 a share, on revenue of $ 1.89 billion. At <LOCATION> Kalamazoo </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Mich.-based </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Upjohn </ORGANIZATION>, second quarter earnings rose 12 percent to $ 87.8 million, or 47 cents a share, from $ 78.6 million, or 42 cents a share a year ago. Revenue totaled $ 721.6 million, up 10 percent from $ 655.5 million in the second quarter of 1987. Earnings for the first six months of the year reached $ 183.2 million, or 98 cents a share, on sales of $ 1.38 billion, up from $ 159.5 million, or 85 cents a share, on sales of $ 1.26 billion in the first half of 1987.
